wfCctOptsEntry.name: wfCctOptsEntry
wfCctOptsEntry.description: Entry format for the table of circuit options

wfCctOptsDelete.name: wfCctOptsDelete
wfCctOptsDelete.description: Creation and deletion flag for this record

wfCctOptsHighPriorityQueueLimit.name: wfCctOptsHighPriorityQueueLimit
wfCctOptsHighPriorityQueueLimit.description: High Priority Queue limit The minimum valid value is zero. no maximum valid value (limited by bufs for the slot)

wfCctOptsNormalPriorityQueueLimit.name: wfCctOptsNormalPriorityQueueLimit
wfCctOptsNormalPriorityQueueLimit.description: Normal Priority Queue limit The minimum valid value is zero. no maximum valid value (limited by bufs for the slot)

wfCctOptsLowPriorityQueueLimit.name: wfCctOptsLowPriorityQueueLimit
wfCctOptsLowPriorityQueueLimit.description: Low Priority Queue limit The minimum valid value is zero. no maximum valid value (limited by bufs for the slot)

wfCctOptsHighWaterPktsClear.name: wfCctOptsHighWaterPktsClear
wfCctOptsHighWaterPktsClear.description: Attribute to clear the high-water marks. When the MIB changes, Priority Queueing (if ENABLED) checks to see if HighWaterPktsClear is different than the last time the MIB was modified in any way. If it is different, all the high water marks (see above) are set to zero.

wfCctOptsDroppedPkts.name: wfCctOptsDroppedPkts
wfCctOptsDroppedPkts.description: Packets which were filtered in Priority Queueing

wfCctOptsLargePkts.name: wfCctOptsLargePkts
wfCctOptsLargePkts.description: Large Packets which became an exception to latency rules

wfCctOptsChooserType.name: wfCctOptsChooserType
wfCctOptsChooserType.description: Algorithm to choose line within a multiline circuit

wfCctOptsPqDequeueAlgType.name: wfCctOptsPqDequeueAlgType
wfCctOptsPqDequeueAlgType.description: Selection of Priority Queueing dequeueing algorithm PQ_STRICT_PRIORITIZATION is 'classical' 7.50 dequeueing. PQ_BANDWIDTH_ALLOCATION makes exceptions to strict prioritization in order to prevent starvation of the Normal and/or Low priority traffic.

wfCctOptsHiPercent.name: wfCctOptsHiPercent
wfCctOptsHiPercent.description: This is the percent of the SYNC line bandwidth that the network manager wishes to allocate to traffic which has been configured to be High Priority. This parameter only has meaning when the bandwidth allocation dequeueing algorithm is enabled by setting the dequeueing algorithm type appropriately. With this parameter set other than 100, each time the configured percent utilization is reached, Normal and Low traffic is sent out (if any is queued up), up to their configured percentages.

wfCctOptsNormalPercent.name: wfCctOptsNormalPercent
wfCctOptsNormalPercent.description: The minimum percent of the SYNC line that Normal-priority traffic will get (if there is any) when the Bandwidth Allocation feature is enabled. See text for wfCctOptsHiPercent for more information.

wfCctOptsLoPercent.name: wfCctOptsLoPercent
wfCctOptsLoPercent.description: The minimum percent of the SYNC line that Low-priority traffic will get (if there is any) when the Bandwidth Allocation feature is enabled. See text for wfCctOptsHiPercent for more information.

wfCctOptsHiTotalOctets.name: wfCctOptsHiTotalOctets
wfCctOptsHiTotalOctets.description: Running total of High Octets transmitted when using Bandwidth Allocation dequeueing algorithm

wfCctOptsNormalTotalOctets.name: wfCctOptsNormalTotalOctets
wfCctOptsNormalTotalOctets.description: Running total of Normal Octets transmitted when using Bandwidth Allocation dequeueing algorithm

wfCctOptsLoTotalOctets.name: wfCctOptsLoTotalOctets
wfCctOptsLoTotalOctets.description: Running total of Low Octets transmitted when using Bandwidth Allocation dequeueing algorithm

wfCctOptsPrimaryCctWanProtocolType.name: wfCctOptsPrimaryCctWanProtocolType
wfCctOptsPrimaryCctWanProtocolType.description: The type of WAN protocol type which is running on the primary line. This attribute is only read when a dial backup circuit is using this mib record.

wfCctOptsMacFilterFormat.name: wfCctOptsMacFilterFormat
wfCctOptsMacFilterFormat.description: Used to force the Mac src/dst address to be matched in Token Ring format.

wfCctOptsPktsNotQueued.name: wfCctOptsPktsNotQueued
wfCctOptsPktsNotQueued.description: Packets that were not Queued or Dropped by Priority Queuing

wfCctOptsBitsShiftCount.name: wfCctOptsBitsShiftCount
wfCctOptsBitsShiftCount.description: Used to shift src/dst address to the right when addressed based chooser is set.

wfCctOptsFrSetDeLowQ.name: wfCctOptsFrSetDeLowQ
wfCctOptsFrSetDeLowQ.description: Used on Frame Relay interfaces, allows Set of DE ( Discard Eligible ) bit of packets that end up in PQ's Low Queue, the Default is Do Set DE bit

wfCctOptsFrSetDeNormQ.name: wfCctOptsFrSetDeNormQ
wfCctOptsFrSetDeNormQ.description: Used on Frame Relay interfaces, allows Set of DE ( Discard Eligible ) bit of packets that end up in PQ's Normal Queue, the Default is Don't Set DE bit

wfCctOptsShapedPriorityQueueLimit.name: wfCctOptsShapedPriorityQueueLimit
wfCctOptsShapedPriorityQueueLimit.description: Frame Relay Traffic Shaping Priority Queue Limit. the minimum valid value is zerom no maximum valid value (limited by bufs for the slot).

wfCctOptsMaxShapedPriorityQueueLatency.name: wfCctOptsMaxShapedPriorityQueueLatency
wfCctOptsMaxShapedPriorityQueueLatency.description: Frame Relay Traffic Shaping Priority Queue Latency.

wfCctOptsShapedXmits.name: wfCctOptsShapedXmits
wfCctOptsShapedXmits.description: Frame Relay Traffic Shaping Priority Transmit count.

wfCctOptsShapedClippedPkts.name: wfCctOptsShapedClippedPkts
wfCctOptsShapedClippedPkts.description: Frame Relay Traffic Shaping Transmit Clip count.

wfCctOptsShapedQHighWaterPkts.name: wfCctOptsShapedQHighWaterPkts
wfCctOptsShapedQHighWaterPkts.description: Frame Relay Traffic Shaping Queue high-water mark.

wfCctOptsShapedTotalOctets.name: wfCctOptsShapedTotalOctets
wfCctOptsShapedTotalOctets.description: Running total of Frame Relay Traffic Shaping octets transmitted.

wfDequeueAtLineRate.name: wfDequeueAtLineRate
wfDequeueAtLineRate.description: Determines whether the dequeuing from the queues is to be done at the line rate instead of the conventional technique or not.

wfCctOptsBrFilterCreate.name: wfCctOptsBrFilterCreate
wfCctOptsBrFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfCctOptsBrFilterEnable.name: wfCctOptsBrFilterEnable
wfCctOptsBrFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfCctOptsBrFilterState.name: wfCctOptsBrFilterState
wfCctOptsBrFilterState.description: Defines the current State of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfCctOptsBrFilterCounter.name: wfCctOptsBrFilterCounter
wfCctOptsBrFilterCounter.description: The number of received packets that have matched this rule.

wfCctOptsBrFilterCct.name: wfCctOptsBrFilterCct
wfCctOptsBrFilterCct.description: The ID of the CctBridge Cct to which the filter is applied.

wfCctOptsIpFilterCreate.name: wfCctOptsIpFilterCreate
wfCctOptsIpFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfCctOptsIpFilterEnable.name: wfCctOptsIpFilterEnable
wfCctOptsIpFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfCctOptsIpFilterState.name: wfCctOptsIpFilterState
wfCctOptsIpFilterState.description: Defines the current State of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfCctOptsIpFilterCounter.name: wfCctOptsIpFilterCounter
wfCctOptsIpFilterCounter.description: The number of received packets that have matched this rule.

wfCctOptsIpFilterCct.name: wfCctOptsIpFilterCct
wfCctOptsIpFilterCct.description: The ID of the CctIp Cct to which the filter is applied.

wfCctOptsLengthBasedDelete.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedDelete
wfCctOptsLengthBasedDelete.description: Defines the existence of the length based priority filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfCctOptsLengthBasedDisable.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedDisable
wfCctOptsLengthBasedDisable.description: Defines whether or not the length based priority filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfCctOptsLengthBasedState.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedState
wfCctOptsLengthBasedState.description: Defines the current State of the length based priority filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfCctOptsLengthBasedCct.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedCct
wfCctOptsLengthBasedCct.description: The ID of the Cct to which the filter is applied

wfCctOptsLengthBasedData.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedData
wfCctOptsLengthBasedData.description: a five byte quantity of the form ethernet - 0x6003000000 (e.g. DECnet) lsap - 0xfefe030000 (e.g. OSI) snap - 0x0000000800 (e.g. IP) - 0x0800070800 (e.g. Appletalk DDP)

wfCctOptsLengthBasedLength.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedLength
wfCctOptsLengthBasedLength.description: Maximum length of a packet to be considered high priority

wfCctOptsLengthBasedLessThanQ.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedLessThanQ
wfCctOptsLengthBasedLessThanQ.description: queue into which packets of length less than or equal wfCctOptsLengthBasedLength are placed

wfCctOptsLengthBasedGreaterThanQ.name: wfCctOptsLengthBasedGreaterThanQ
wfCctOptsLengthBasedGreaterThanQ.description: queue into which packets of length greater than wfCctOptsLengthBasedLength are placed

wfSwservOptsTable.description: The table of circuits defined over switched services

wfSwservOptsEntry.description: Entry format for the table of sw_serv circuit options

wfSwservOptsBackupCct.name: wfSwservOptsBackupCct

wfSwservOptsBackupMode.name: wfSwservOptsBackupMode
wfSwservOptsBackupMode.description: Mode Master ( initiate dialing ) or Slave

wfSwservOptsMaxUpTime.name: wfSwservOptsMaxUpTime
wfSwservOptsMaxUpTime.description: Max amount fo time dial call can exist

wfSwservOptsBringUpHour.name: wfSwservOptsBringUpHour
wfSwservOptsBringUpHour.description: Time of day hour to allow a line to dial

wfSwservOptsBringUpMinute.name: wfSwservOptsBringUpMinute
wfSwservOptsBringUpMinute.description: Time of day minute to allow a line to dial

wfSwservOptsTakeDownHour.name: wfSwservOptsTakeDownHour
wfSwservOptsTakeDownHour.description: Time of day hour to take down a dial line

wfSwservOptsTakeDownMinute.name: wfSwservOptsTakeDownMinute
wfSwservOptsTakeDownMinute.description: Time of day minute to take down a dial line

wfSwservOptsInactivityTime.name: wfSwservOptsInactivityTime
wfSwservOptsInactivityTime.description: Maximum for inactivity timer is equal to infinity = 99999999

wfSwservOptsPrimaryDownTime.name: wfSwservOptsPrimaryDownTime
wfSwservOptsPrimaryDownTime.description: Amount of time allowed for establishment of primary before the backup is invoked

wfSwservOptsNumOutgoingConn.name: wfSwservOptsNumOutgoingConn
wfSwservOptsNumOutgoingConn.description: Number of Outgoing call attempts for this circuit

wfSwservOptsNumIncomingConn.name: wfSwservOptsNumIncomingConn
wfSwservOptsNumIncomingConn.description: Number of Incoming call attempts for this circuit

wfSwservOptsActiveSlot.name: wfSwservOptsActiveSlot
wfSwservOptsActiveSlot.description: Slot actively in use by this call

wfSwservOptsActiveLine.name: wfSwservOptsActiveLine
wfSwservOptsActiveLine.description: Line actively in use by this call

wfSwservOptsPacketsDropped.name: wfSwservOptsPacketsDropped
wfSwservOptsPacketsDropped.description: Number of Incoming call attempts for this circuit

wfSwservOptsTimeLastPktDropped.name: wfSwservOptsTimeLastPktDropped
wfSwservOptsTimeLastPktDropped.description: Number of Incoming call attempts for this circuit

wfSwservOptsRetryDelay.name: wfSwservOptsRetryDelay
wfSwservOptsRetryDelay.description: delay to wait after retrys fails. value is in seconds

wfSwservOptsDemandConnectionMode.name: wfSwservOptsDemandConnectionMode
wfSwservOptsDemandConnectionMode.description: Mode Master - outgoing call has precedence terminate incoming call Slave - incoming call has precedence terminate outgoing call NO_Dial - if data is present do MOT establish connection just drop the data

wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermination.name: wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermination
wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermination.description: Automatically terminates demand circuit if maximum connect attempts reached

wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermReset.name: wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermReset
wfSwservOptsAutoDemandTermReset.description: Amount of time ( in Minutes )before atttempting to recreate the demand circuit after an auto termination

wfSwservOptsChapLocalName.name: wfSwservOptsChapLocalName
wfSwservOptsChapLocalName.description: This attribute is used to assign a local CHAP Name to outbound calls to to inform our peer of our identity, during WHOAMI processing

wfSwservOptsChapSecret.name: wfSwservOptsChapSecret
wfSwservOptsChapSecret.description: Secret used for running CHAP when this cct is active. The peer must use the same secret when responding to our Challenges, which will be found in the Whoami Table

wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermination.name: wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermination
wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermination.description: Automatically terminates demand circuit if maximum connect attempts reached

wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermReset.name: wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermReset
wfSwservOptsMaxUpTermReset.description: Amount of time ( in Minutes )before atttempting to recreate the demand circuit after an auto termination

wfSwservOptsBandwidthMode.name: wfSwservOptsBandwidthMode
wfSwservOptsBandwidthMode.description: Bandwidth Mode Monitor (Congestion Monitor) or NORMAL

wfSwservOptsPapId.name: wfSwservOptsPapId
wfSwservOptsPapId.description: This attribute is used to assign a local PAP Id to outbound calls to to inform our peer of our identity, during WHOAMI processing

wfSwservOptsPapPassword.name: wfSwservOptsPapPassword
wfSwservOptsPapPassword.description: This attribute is used to assign a local PAP Password to outbound calls to to inform our peer of our identity, during WHOAMI processing

wfSwservOptsDebugMsgLevel.name: wfSwservOptsDebugMsgLevel
wfSwservOptsDebugMsgLevel.description: This attribute is used to assign the level of Swserv Debug message to be logged for the circuit

wfSwservOptsDmdCctGroupNum.name: wfSwservOptsDmdCctGroupNum
wfSwservOptsDmdCctGroupNum.description: Backup Circuit Number assigned by site manager

wfSwservOptsWanProtocol.name: wfSwservOptsWanProtocol
wfSwservOptsWanProtocol.description: Wan Protocol for this circuit assigned by site manager. Used by BNX Software to Support ISDN Switched access to Frame Relay Switch Network.

wfSwservOptsSecondaryCct.name: wfSwservOptsSecondaryCct
wfSwservOptsSecondaryCct.description: Secondary circuit to be used by Line Manager when creating a backup for this primary circuit.

wfSwservOptsPoolLineNumber.name: wfSwservOptsPoolLineNumber
wfSwservOptsPoolLineNumber.description: Pooling line number used for identifying Frame Relay backup interface objects associated with a pool.

wfSwservOptsPoolLineIndex.name: wfSwservOptsPoolLineIndex
wfSwservOptsPoolLineIndex.description: Lower layer index used for identifying Frame Relay backup interface objects associated with a pool.

wfSwservOptsMinDuration.name: wfSwservOptsMinDuration
wfSwservOptsMinDuration.description: Maximum for min duration timer in seconds is equal to infinity = 99999999, min is 10

wfSwservOptsOutboundAuth.name: wfSwservOptsOutboundAuth
wfSwservOptsOutboundAuth.description: Allows the disabling of Authentication when the router is placing an outbound call.

wfSwservOptsOverSubRetryTimer.name: wfSwservOptsOverSubRetryTimer
wfSwservOptsOverSubRetryTimer.description: This parameter allows the user to cofigure the time period at which a connection will be retried, if a previous connection attempt for routing updates failed due to lack of line resources. This time should be less than the stabilization timer for IP/IPX protocols. This time is expressed in minutes and is meaningful only if Dial Optimized Routing is enabled.

wfSwservOptsStandbyMode.name: wfSwservOptsStandbyMode
wfSwservOptsStandbyMode.description: This parameter allows a demand circuit to be identified as standby or demand. The hot standby circuit is down until an event invokes it. Normal standby is invoked manually or by an incoming call.

wfSwservOptsStandbyFailBackMode.name: wfSwservOptsStandbyFailBackMode
wfSwservOptsStandbyFailBackMode.description: This parameter is used to indicate if standby failback should be automatic or manual.

wfSwservOptsManualStandbyAction.name: wfSwservOptsManualStandbyAction
wfSwservOptsManualStandbyAction.description: This parameter is used to manually activate and deactivate a standby circuit.

wfSwservOptsCallbackMode.name: wfSwservOptsCallbackMode
wfSwservOptsCallbackMode.description: Defines the role this circuit will play in Callback. INACTIVE disables Callback on this circuit. SERVER performs Callback via Outgoing Phone Number. CLIENT circuit expects peer to perform Callback. SERVER_CALLID performs Callback via ANI

wfSwservOptsCallbackServerDelay.name: wfSwservOptsCallbackServerDelay
wfSwservOptsCallbackServerDelay.description: The amount of time the CALLBACK_SERVER will wait, (in seconds) before performing Callback,dialing back the initial caller. The default time is 0, however modem connections may need some delay configured to prevent busy situations.

wfSwservOptsCallbackClientDelay.name: wfSwservOptsCallbackClientDelay
wfSwservOptsCallbackClientDelay.description: The amount of time the CALLBACK_CLIENT will wait, (in seconds) for its peer to perform Callback. Data ariving during opperation of the timer, will not cause a connection to be established.

wfSwservOptsQueueSize.name: wfSwservOptsQueueSize
wfSwservOptsQueueSize.description: This parameter controls the length of the queue used for dial services.

wfSwservOptsDequeueWaitTimer.name: wfSwservOptsDequeueWaitTimer
wfSwservOptsDequeueWaitTimer.description: This parameter controls the time FR waits before dequeuing data for FRDOD.

wfSwservOptsMru.name: wfSwservOptsMru
wfSwservOptsMru.description: This is the MRU being used for this demand circuit.

wfSwservOptsBootupDelay.name: wfSwservOptsBootupDelay
wfSwservOptsBootupDelay.description: Delay in initiation of the DoD circuit at bootup time

wfSwservOptsCallbackOptRfc1570.name: wfSwservOptsCallbackOptRfc1570
wfSwservOptsCallbackOptRfc1570.description: The PPP/LCP Callback Option; indicates the type of data content the callback client places in wfSwservOptsCallbackDataRfc1570 for the callback server

wfSwservOptsCallbackDataRfc1570.name: wfSwservOptsCallbackDataRfc1570
wfSwservOptsCallbackDataRfc1570.description: The PPP/LCP Callback Data; the actual callback client data which is sent to the callback server for processing

wfSwservOutPhoneNumEntry.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumEntry
wfSwservOutPhoneNumEntry.description: An entry in the SWSERV_SYNC table

wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelete.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelete
wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelete.description: Delete this phone number from the list

wfSwservOutPhoneNumCct.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumCct
wfSwservOutPhoneNumCct.description: CCT number for this phone list instance

wfSwservOutPhoneNumIndex.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumIndex
wfSwservOutPhoneNumIndex.description: a unique one up type number to create a list

wfSwservOutPhoneNumRmtStationNum.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumRmtStationNum
wfSwservOutPhoneNumRmtStationNum.description: the station address (phone number) of the remote system

wfSwservOutPhoneNumSubAddr.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumSubAddr
wfSwservOutPhoneNumSubAddr.description: for Swserv phone numbers, the sub address portion

wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelimiter.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelimiter
wfSwservOutPhoneNumDelimiter.description: for Swserv phone numbers, the delimiter portion

wfSwservOutPhoneNumType.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumType
wfSwservOutPhoneNumType.description: phone number types; ISDN types, Modem Sync Dial or Async Dial types

wfSwservOutPhoneNumTypeofNum.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumTypeofNum
wfSwservOutPhoneNumTypeofNum.description: IF ISDN type number, it needs type of number UNKNOWN Type is 0, use 1 to satisfy MDL requirement This attribute value will be ANDED with 0xFFF0 before using it.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumPlan.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumPlan
wfSwservOutPhoneNumPlan.description: If Isdn and if type of number is UNKNOWN or INERNATIONAL or NATIONAL or SUBSCRIBER then a plan number is needed. UNKNOWN is 0 , using 16 (0x10)to satisfy MDL requirement. We will AND this field with 0x0F before using it.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumRateAdaption.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumRateAdaption
wfSwservOutPhoneNumRateAdaption.description: If Isdn and if a specifis Transfer rate is to be requested when establishing a call to this distination address specify the desired rate.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumRemotePoolType.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumRemotePoolType
wfSwservOutPhoneNumRemotePoolType.description: Specify the types of calls accepted by the remote router on this port. For example, if the port on the remote router resides in only a demand pool specify the port type for this phone number to be dialondemand.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumConnectionType.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumConnectionType
wfSwservOutPhoneNumConnectionType.description: Specify if this phone number can be used to receive a single call or multiple calls.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumChannelType.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumChannelType
wfSwservOutPhoneNumChannelType.description: Type of Channels used for the outgoing call.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumPrefix.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumPrefix
wfSwservOutPhoneNumPrefix.description: Phone number prefix such as hayes dial command.

wfSwservOutPhoneNumBearerService.name: wfSwservOutPhoneNumBearerService
wfSwservOutPhoneNumBearerService.description: The Bearer service - data or voice, for ISDN call setup using this number

wfSwservInPhoneNumEntry.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumEntry
wfSwservInPhoneNumEntry.description: An entry in the Swserv_SYNC table

wfSwservInPhoneNumDelete.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumDelete
wfSwservInPhoneNumDelete.description: Delete this phone number from the list

wfSwservInPhoneNumIndex.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumIndex
wfSwservInPhoneNumIndex.description: a unique one up type number to create a list

wfSwservInPhoneNumRmtStationNum.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumRmtStationNum
wfSwservInPhoneNumRmtStationNum.description: the station address (phone number) of the remote system

wfSwservInPhoneNumSubAddr.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumSubAddr
wfSwservInPhoneNumSubAddr.description: for Swserv phone numbers, the sub address portion

wfSwservInPhoneNumDelimiter.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumDelimiter
wfSwservInPhoneNumDelimiter.description: for Swserv phone numbers, the delimiter portion

wfSwservInPhoneNumType.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumType
wfSwservInPhoneNumType.description: phone number types; ISDN types or Modem Dial types

wfSwservInPhoneNumTypeofNum.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumTypeofNum
wfSwservInPhoneNumTypeofNum.description: We will AND this field with 0x0xFFF0 before using it.

wfSwservInPhoneNumCct.name: wfSwservInPhoneNumCct
wfSwservInPhoneNumCct.description: Identifies which circuit should be used when performing Callback. If Null, Authentication must complete before Callback can occur.

wfCctOptsBrBuPppFilterTable.name: wfCctOptsBrBuPppFilterTable
wfCctOptsBrBuPppFilterTable.description: Dial Backup PPP Datalink filter table

wfCctOptsBrBuPppFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterCreate.description: Defines the existence of the traffic filter rule: created - traffic filter exists delete - traffic filter does not exist and can be deleted.

wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterEnable.description: Defines whether or not the traffic filter rule should be used: enabled - activate the rule. disabled - inactivate the rule.

wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterState.name: wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterState
wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterState.description: Defines the current State of the traffic filter: inactive - the rule is not in use. active - the rule is being used. error - the application detected an error in the rule.

wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterCounter.name: wfCctOptsIpBuPppFilterCounter

wfCctOptsCngcDelete.name: wfCctOptsCngcDelete

wfCctOptsCngcDisable.name: wfCctOptsCngcDisable
wfCctOptsCngcDisable.description: Defines whether congestion control is enabled or disabled on the circuit

wfCctOptsCngcCct.name: wfCctOptsCngcCct
wfCctOptsCngcCct.description: The circuit number of the circuit to which the entry is applied

wfCctOptsCngcSmdsDiscardability.name: wfCctOptsCngcSmdsDiscardability
wfCctOptsCngcSmdsDiscardability.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines how SMDS packets entering BNX network through SMDS SSI and SMDS SNI interfaces should be treated at this circuit during congestion for dropping. This is applicable only on the internodal links. CNGC_FRDE - treat this like Frame relay DE frame. CNGC_FRNDE - treat this like Frame Relay non DE frame CNGC_DATAGRAM - treat this like a datagram packet.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgSwtxqThreshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgSwtxqThreshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgSwtxqThreshold.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines the user configured software transmit queue threshold. If this is set to NULL_VAL then the switch calculates the default value depending on the media and uses the default value. The default value is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcSwtxqThreshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcSwtxqThreshold
wfCctOptsCngcSwtxqThreshold.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines the software transmit queue threshold in use. Switch updates this attribute to inform user what the current software transmit queue threshold is.

wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel0Threshold.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines the Software Transmit Queue congestion level 0 threshold as a percentage of the Software Transmit Queue Threshold. The default value is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel1Threshold.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines the Software Transmit Queue congestion level 1 threshold as a percentage of the Software Transmit Queue Threshold. The default value is recommended. wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel1Threshold should be more than wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel0Threshold, otherwise there will be no congestion level 1.

wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel2Threshold.description: This is obsolete in V5.0 and upwards. Defines the Software Transmit Queue congestion level 2 threshold as a percentage of the Software Transmit Queue Threshold. The default value is recommended. wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel2Threshold should be more than wfCctOptsCngcCngLevel1Threshold, otherwise there will be no congestion level 2.

wfCctOptsCngcLinkType.name: wfCctOptsCngcLinkType
wfCctOptsCngcLinkType.description: Defines whether the circuit is an access link or inter-nodal link (trunk). Traffic monitoring, traffic priority determination, traffic discardability level determination are done at access link and each incoming packet on an access link is tagged with the information. Inter-nodal link (trunk) uses the above tagged information in packets for priority queueing and discarding packets during congestion. WARNING - It is important to set the appropriate link type for this attribute otherwise congestion control will not work. The default value for this attribute is access link. This attribute value must be changed to CNGC_LINK_INTER_NODAL for inter-nodal link(trunk).

wfCctOptsCngcTrfPriorityEnable.name: wfCctOptsCngcTrfPriorityEnable
wfCctOptsCngcTrfPriorityEnable.description: Defines whether traffic prioritization is enabled or disabled on the circuit.

wfCctOptsCngcPortIPTrfPriority.name: wfCctOptsCngcPortIPTrfPriority
wfCctOptsCngcPortIPTrfPriority.description: Defines the traffic priority for transmitting Non Frame Relay or SMDS traffic on this port. CNGC_IPPRIORITY_TWO - Default Value Set all non FR or SMDS user traffic packets to priority 2. CNGC_IPPRIORITY_ONE - Set all non FR or SMDS packets to priority 1. CNGC_IPPRIORITY_TWO - Set all non FR or SMDS packets to priority 2. CNGC_IPPRIORITY_THREE - Set all non FR or SMDS packets to priority 3.

wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfDiscardLvl.name: wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfDiscardLvl
wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfDiscardLvl.description: Defines at what congestion level the incoming packets on this port should be discarded in the network. CNGC_DISCARD_AT_LVL_TWO - Discard FR DE packets at level 2, discard FR non DE packets at level 4, discard SMDS packets at level 3, discard IP packets at level 3. Default value CNGC_DISCARD_AT_LVL_ONE - discard all at level 1 CNGC_DISCARD_AT_LVL_TWO - discard all at level 2 CNGC_DISCARD_AT_LVL_THREE - discard all at level 3 CNGC_DISCARD_AT_LVL_FOUR - discard all at level 4

wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfPriority.name: wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfPriority
wfCctOptsCngcPortTrfPriority.description: Defines the traffic priority level of all the incoming packets on this port. CNGC_PRIORITY_TWO - Default value Set all incoming user traffic packets to priority 2. CNGC_PRIORITY_ONE - Set all incoming packets to priority 1. CNGC_PRIORITY_TWO - Set all incoming packets to priority 2. CNGC_PRIORITY_THREE - Set all incoming packets to priority 3. Priority 0 is reserved for network critical packets like OSPF, FR LMI and SMDS heartbeat, Cross Net polling and is not available for user traffic.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgHwtxQThreshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgHwtxQThreshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgHwtxQThreshold.description: Defines the user configured hardware transmit queue threshold. NULL_VAL - Switch calculates the appropriate value based on system resources and uses the value. This is recommended. CNGC_HWTXQ_MINIMUM - minimum value to be used. CNGC_HWTXQ_MAXIMUM - maximum value to be used.

wfCctOptsCngcSndTrapForPktsDropped.name: wfCctOptsCngcSndTrapForPktsDropped
wfCctOptsCngcSndTrapForPktsDropped.description: Switch sends a congestion notification trap for every wfCctOptsCngcSndTrapForPktsDropped number of packets dropped.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp0Threshold.description: Defines the Priority 0 queue threshold NULL_VAL - Switch calculates the appropriate value based on system resources and uses the value. This is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl0Threshold.description: Defines priority 0 queue congestion level 0 threshold as a percentage of priority 0 queue threshold.

wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl1Threshold.description: Defines priority 0 queue congestion level 1 threshold as a percentage of priority 0 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl0Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 0 queue congestion level 1.

wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl2Threshold.description: Defines priority 0 queue congestion level 2 threshold as a percentage of priority 0 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp0CngLvl1Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 0 queue congestion level 2.

wfCctOptsCngcQp0PktsServPriNxtQ.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp0PktsServPriNxtQ
wfCctOptsCngcQp0PktsServPriNxtQ.description: Defines the number of priority 0 queue packets to be served prior to serving each priority 1 queue packet. If priority 0 queue is empty then priority 1 queue packets are served.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp1Threshold.description: Defines the Priority 1 queue threshold NULL_VAL - Switch calculates the appropriate value based on system resources and uses the value. This is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl0Threshold.description: Defines priority 1 queue congestion level 0 threshold as a percentage of priority 1 queue threshold.

wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl1Threshold.description: Defines priority 1 queue congestion level 1 threshold as a percentage of priority 1 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl0Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 1 queue congestion level 1.

wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl2Threshold.description: Defines priority 1 queue congestion level 2 threshold as a percentage of priority 1 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp1CngLvl1Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 1 queue congestion level 2.

wfCctOptsCngcQp1PktsServPriNxtQ.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp1PktsServPriNxtQ
wfCctOptsCngcQp1PktsServPriNxtQ.description: Defines the number of priority 1 queue packets to be served prior to serving each priority 2 queue packet. If priority 1 queue is empty then priority 2 queue packets are served.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp2Threshold.description: Defines the Priority 2 queue threshold NULL_VAL - Switch calculates the appropriate value based on system resources and uses the value. This is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl0Threshold.description: Defines priority 2 queue congestion level 0 threshold as a percentage of priority 2 queue threshold.

wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl1Threshold.description: Defines priority 2 queue congestion level 1 threshold as a percentage of priority 2 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl0Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 2 queue congestion level 1.

wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl2Threshold.description: Defines priority 2 queue congestion level 2 threshold as a percentage of priority 2 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp2CngLvl1Threshold, otherwise there wil be no priority 2 queue congestion level 2.

wfCctOptsCngcQp2PktsServPriNxtQ.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp2PktsServPriNxtQ
wfCctOptsCngcQp2PktsServPriNxtQ.description: Defines the number of priority 2 queue packets to be served prior to serving each priority 3 queue packet. If priority 2 queue is empty then priority 3 queue packets are served.

wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp3Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp3Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcCfgQp3Threshold.description: Defines the Priority 3 queue threshold NULL_VAL - Switch calculates the appropriate value based on system resources and uses the value. This is recommended.

wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl0Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl0Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl0Threshold.description: Defines priority 3 queue congestion level 0 threshold as a percentage of priority 3 queue threshold.

wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl1Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl1Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl1Threshold.description: Defines priority 3 queue congestion level 1 threshold as a percentage of priority 3 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl0Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 3 queue congestion level 1.

wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl2Threshold.name: wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl2Threshold
wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl2Threshold.description: Defines priority 3 queue congestion level 2 threshold as a percentage of priority 3 queue threshold. The value of this attribute should be greater than wfCctOptsCngcQp3CngLvl1Threshold, otherwise there will be no priority 3 queue congestion level 2.

wfCctOptsCngcTxFRNonDePkts.description: Number of Frame Relay non DE packets transmitted

wfCctOptsCngcDropFRDeOctets.description: number of Frame Relay DE octets dropped

wfCctOptsCngcFRSetFecnPkts.name: wfCctOptsCngcFRSetFecnPkts
wfCctOptsCngcFRSetFecnPkts.description: number of Frame Relay packets in which this link set FECN

wfCctOptsCngcFRSetFecnOctets.description: number of Frame Relay octets in which this link set FECN

wfCctOptsCngcFRSetBecnPkts.description: number of Frame Relay frames in which this link set BECN

wfCctOptsCngcFRSetBecnOctets.description: number of Frame Relay octets in which this link set BECN

wfCctOptsCngcDropNonFRPkts.description: Number of Non Frame Relay packets dropped

wfCctOptsCngcDropNonFROctets.description: number of Non Frame Relay octets dropped

wfCctOptsCngcLogPower.name: wfCctOptsCngcLogPower
wfCctOptsCngcLogPower.description: This number specifies that the following log events: 1. Dropped DE Frame. 2. Dropped Non DE Frames. 3. Set DE Frames. 4. Set FECN/BECN. be logged once every (X) occurances. Where (X) = Base 2 raised to the power. The user specifies the power by setting this wfCctOptsCngcLogPower mib attribute. For example, setting wfCctOptsCngcLogPower to a value of 10 means that a log message will be logged once every 1024 occurances. 1024 = (2 ^ wfCctOptsCngcLogPower) or (2 raised to 10th power). Legal values for this attribute ranges from 10 to 31. This translates to 2^10 (1024) through 2^31 (2147483648). Default: 2^31.

wfSwservTODDelete.name: wfSwservTODDelete
wfSwservTODDelete.description: Delete time of day instance from the list for this circuit

wfSwservTODCct.description: CCT number for time of day instance

wfSwservTODIndex.description: a unique number to specify instance

wfSwservTODStartTime.name: wfSwservTODStartTime
wfSwservTODStartTime.description: Start Time of day allow a line to dial ( HHMM format )

wfSwservTODEndTime.name: wfSwservTODEndTime
wfSwservTODEndTime.description: End Time of day connection can be active for specified circuit ( HHMM format )

wfSwservTODInactivityEnable.name: wfSwservTODInactivityEnable
wfSwservTODInactivityEnable.description: Inactivity Timer if disabled the inactivity timer is ignored during this time period, if enabled the connection is brought down due to inactivity. If this parameter is DISABLED, the circuit will be established automatically during the configured times, regardless of the Availability Mode.

wfSwservTODAvailabilityMode.name: wfSwservTODAvailabilityMode
wfSwservTODAvailabilityMode.description: Set this field to AVAILABLE to allow the circuit to be established between the configured start and end times. Set it to NOT AVAILABLE to prevent the circuit from being established during those times. Inactivity Timeout must be ENABLED for Availability Mode to have any effect. If Inactivity Timeout is DISABLED, the circuit will be established automatically during the configured times, regardless of the Availability Mode.

wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackMode.name: wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackMode
wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackMode.description: Indicates if failback mode for this time of day range. When set to automatic circuit will failback subject to the failback timer. When set to manual circuit will not failback.

wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackTime.name: wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackTime
wfSwservTODStandbyFailBackTime.description: Indicates number of minutes to wait after the primary is observed as active before deactivating the standby. Default value of 0 disables failback timer.
